HEADWORD: Eosin
<hw>E"o*sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ dawn.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow or brownish red dyestuff obtained by
the action of bromine on fluoresce⟦ium⟧n, and named from the fine
rose-red which it imparts to silk. It is also used for making a fine red
ink. Its solution is fluorescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

